Look at the flower blossoms.

869
00:44:27,320 --> 00:44:28,240
I heard that Young Madam Ou

870
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:29,640
is a connoisseur

871
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:31,400
who knows a lot
about flowers and plants.

872
00:44:31,600 --> 00:44:33,600
Would you give me a few pointers?

873
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:36,320
Young Madam Wang,
you do me too much honor.

874
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:38,160
I'm not an expert in the field.

875
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:40,360
I just know a thing or two about it.

876
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:42,080
Look at this flower.

877
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:45,720
It is scarlet,
with numerous layers of petals.

878
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:47,280
This is...

879
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:53,360
Madam Xu,

880
00:44:53,880 --> 00:44:55,440
I believe you know

881
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:58,280
what the flower is.

882
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:08,280
It is a very rare color.

883
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:09,360
Madam,

884
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:11,080
do you think

885
00:45:11,280 --> 00:45:11,960
you are more knowledgeable

886
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:13,400
than the wife

887
00:45:13,680 --> 00:45:15,200
of Marquis Yongping?

888
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:20,440
Great Madam, should we...

889
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:25,240
Young Madam Ou,

890
00:45:25,440 --> 00:45:26,920
I beg to differ.

891
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:29,200
Everyone has his own
strengths and weaknesses.

892
00:45:29,600 --> 00:45:31,240
Nobody is omniscient.

893
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:32,800
It is just a flower.

894
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,240
What difference does it make

895
00:45:34,520 --> 00:45:35,680
if I don't know its type?

896
00:45:35,960 --> 00:45:38,320
Even if I know, does it
make me superior to others?

897
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:40,800
It turns out that

898
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:42,080
being the wife of Marquis Yongping

899
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:42,920
makes no change

900
00:45:43,120 --> 00:45:44,880
to one's lowness and shallowness.

901
00:45:45,120 --> 00:45:46,720
You're pathetically ignorant.

902
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:47,440
Don't refer to yourself

903
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:49,200
as the daughter of Luo family.

904
00:45:50,880 --> 00:45:51,840
As far as I'm concerned,

905
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:54,200
one brings shame to the family

906
00:45:54,400 --> 00:45:55,960
when she plays against
her own family members.

907
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:57,080
Erniang.

908
00:45:58,760 --> 00:46:00,480
Madam Xu,

909
00:46:00,680 --> 00:46:02,200
I beg to differ.

910
00:46:02,520 --> 00:46:04,240
We should admit our ignorance.

911
00:46:04,440 --> 00:46:05,520
How could you

912
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,080
sugarcoat it?

913
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:08,400
Is it what you learned

914
00:46:08,840 --> 00:46:10,760
from Xu family?

915
00:46:12,800 --> 00:46:14,960
People can always learn from each other.

916
00:46:15,320 --> 00:46:17,360
Confucius did not feel ashamed
to ask the two kids

917
00:46:17,560 --> 00:46:18,920
when he saw their debate.

918
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:20,720
If we don't know something,

919
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:22,920
we can always ask.

920
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:24,360
It is not something to be ashamed of.

921
00:46:25,800 --> 00:46:26,560
Now I see.

922
00:46:26,760 --> 00:46:29,280
Madam Xu, you're
comparing yourself to a saint.

923
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:32,520
Young Madam Ou, I'm no match for you

924
00:46:32,720 --> 00:46:34,120
when it comes to

925
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:36,280
taking things out of context.

926
00:46:41,440 --> 00:46:43,200
Why not admit that
you don't know this flower?

927
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,320
Why keep beating around the bush?

928
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:50,760
In spring, there are
peach and plum blossoms.

929
00:46:51,160 --> 00:46:52,480
The scent of cymbidium comes with wind.

930
00:46:53,200 --> 00:46:54,600
The redder the flower is,

931
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:56,720
the more precious the cymbidium is.

932
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:00,560
Though the color is rare,

933
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:03,320
the flower is not unique
to prestigious families.

934
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:05,920
It can also be found in merchant families.

935
00:47:06,720 --> 00:47:08,200
It is nothing but an ornament.

936
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:09,880
I know its type, but what's the point?

937
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:12,280
Merchant families?

938
00:47:12,960 --> 00:47:14,440
How can you mention
our family and merchant families

939
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:16,000
in the same breath?

940
00:47:21,920 --> 00:47:24,040
Red cymbidium is rare.

941
00:47:25,600 --> 00:47:26,960
But people with ulterior motivations

942
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:28,400
are not rare.

943
00:47:29,640 --> 00:47:31,120
Orchid is a noble plant.

944
00:47:31,520 --> 00:47:32,960
Not everyone is qualified

945
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:34,480
to comment on it.

946
00:47:34,920 --> 00:47:35,880
If it falls into

947
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:37,720
the filthy hands,

948
00:47:38,160 --> 00:47:39,360
its nobleness

949
00:47:39,520 --> 00:47:41,480
will be defiled.

950
00:48:04,820 --> 00:48:07,540
♪In the cold darkness of midnight,
a sigh is heard♪

951
00:48:08,180 --> 00:48:10,940
♪Who picked up the paintbrush
to draw loneliness♪

952
00:48:12,260 --> 00:48:18,820
♪In my life, I can draw everything,
but lovesickness♪

953
00:48:19,260 --> 00:48:21,300
♪The mountain city is waiting for rain♪

954
00:48:22,300 --> 00:48:25,900
♪I am waiting for you
to pass in my memory♪

955
00:48:26,340 --> 00:48:32,500
♪The sky is in a more lonely color
than your face♪

956
00:48:32,940 --> 00:48:35,460
♪The wind rises
and the candle light flickers♪

957
00:48:36,380 --> 00:48:38,940
♪The thin clothes
can't stand the cold days♪

958
00:48:40,140 --> 00:48:46,980
♪Full of twists and turns,
fate is untold♪

959
00:48:47,380 --> 00:48:49,580
♪I ground my thoughts into ink♪

960
00:48:50,580 --> 00:48:54,020
♪But I still can't sketch your contours♪

961
00:48:54,540 --> 00:49:00,300
♪How could the ink
and paper exhaust our stories♪

962
00:49:01,140 --> 00:49:08,020
♪Who picked up the pen
to disturb the heart♪

963
00:49:08,380 --> 00:49:15,020
♪Who visited to remind me of the past♪

964
00:49:15,420 --> 00:49:18,740
♪If feelings can be kept in mind,
but cannot be confessed♪

965
00:49:20,100 --> 00:49:22,140
♪I won't escape from whatever end♪

966
00:49:23,620 --> 00:49:29,340
♪In the dim lantern light,
with you there is me♪

967
00:49:29,340 --> 00:49:36,260
♪Who picked up the pen
to set free lonely tears♪

968
00:49:36,500 --> 00:49:43,020
♪Whoever visited my life,
only you stayed all the days♪

969
00:49:43,580 --> 00:49:47,100
♪If the moth doesn't fly into the fire♪

970
00:49:48,180 --> 00:49:51,140
♪How can it be said to be persistent♪

971
00:49:51,620 --> 00:49:59,260
♪Coming to the end of your story,
there is me♪
